TopicTitle: Spontaneous crashes- 'Write to location xxxx' caused an access violation'

Articles.Content:
Been having trouble with 1.05 since I installed it. Frequently, whenever I'm changing situation (launching from VAB, switching spacecraft etc) the game will simply stop and crash to desktop. All the crash logs read the same sort of thing: E.g.

Error occurred at 2015-11-12_154916.

C:\Program Files\KSP_win\KSP.exe, run by Pete.

74% memory in use.

3544 MB physical memory [902 MB free].

0 MB paging file [3893 MB free].

2048 MB user address space [166 MB free].

Write to location 00400000 caused an access violation.

Error occurred at 2015-11-12_160038.

C:\Program Files\KSP_win\KSP.exe, run by Pete.

64% memory in use.

3544 MB physical memory [1254 MB free].

0 MB paging file [4055 MB free].

2048 MB user address space [215 MB free].

Write to location 004a0000 caused an access violation.

Error occurred at 2015-11-12_161928.

C:\Program Files\KSP_win\KSP.exe, run by Pete.

66% memory in use.

3544 MB physical memory [1193 MB free].

0 MB paging file [3979 MB free].

2048 MB user address space [184 MB free].

Write to location 00400000 caused an access violation.

It's getting unplayable due to constantly fighting the crashes, which are more or less predictable.

Are you sure you are not using any mods?

Right now KSP cannot use more than 3.5GB of ram on your system, no matter how much you have, if you put too many mods on it and do nothing to reduce the RAM usage it's going to crash.

This is only an actual bug if you are not using any mods.
Nope, zero mods installed (probably one of the few running mod-free) I have 4gb RAM installed on 32-bit windows so can't use any more.

note: I'm not very experienced at this whole troubleshooting KSP thing, but a first step, try running KSP.exe as an administrator. (navigate to the file, then right click-> run as admin).

If you're still having issues, double check you have free space on your hard drive and run a chkdsk to make sure you don't have corrupt sections.

Running as an admin seems to make things better (more extensive testing needed) but I've still had one instance so far of the standard windows error message "KSP.exe has stopped working..." rather than the KSP-style "Oops! The game crashed"
Considering the amount of RAM on your system is limited I'd advise you to close all other programs when playing KSP

So to follow-up to this, I'm still having the same trouble. I'm not running any other programs while running KSP. I can't install any more RAM as I'm using a 32-bit system and already have 4gb installed. I'm running KSP.exe as an administrator every time.

I can't remember when I actually closed KSP normally as it tends to crash on me every session. Every instance is the same 'write to location (number) caused an access violation'. Still zero mods installed.

There's a few things that might cause this, one is compatibility mode.

If you're using compatibility mode already try disabling it, it'll be in the shortcut for KSP, also some players on Windows 10 say they need to set Windows 8 mode to get KSP to work.

Another is a popular program called Precision X, it hooks into memory and makes KSP crash, actually anything hooking into RAM can do that.

We'd need the full crash folder to find out more, and your dxdiag hardware report as well.

We'd need the full crash folder to find out more, and your dxdiag hardware report as well.

Current situation: Not using compatibility mode (windows 7) not using any of the known troublesome programs, RAM usage is usually around 65% (and can't install any more than the current 4gb anyway). Designing and testing spacecraft is becoming a chore, due to having to reload every time I revert to the VAB.

I've got a whole folder full of crash files I can send to you...

The most recent folder should be enough, it will contain the output_log.txt, error log and a few other files.

We'll also need your dxdiag log, you can run dxdiag from the start menu by typing it in and pressing enter.
I am having this same issue. It seems to happen almost every time I switch between VAB or the space centre or actual gameplay. Also no mods and 32 bit Windows 7.
Please take a look at this thread mc8888, we will need more information from you beginning with your output_log.txt :)
Sorry that link doesn't lead to a thread...

I spoilered your log file Pete, it's the eye icon in the text editor

The log shows a general memory access error (0xc0000005), these could be caused by anything and are non specific.

Mono is provided with KSP and is used for KSP code and for addons.

Next time this happens please post the output_log.txt, there is one in KSP_Data and an identical file in the crash folder.

Don't forget spoilers

5 hours ago, Andem said:

How much RAM can your computer hold? Even though KSP can't use it all Your OS still has to run, and windows background processes is one of my biggest problems

It doesn't matter how much his computer can hold, he's still running a 32-bit OS. 32-Bit OS's are limited to accessing up to 4GB due to memory address limits. Generally, this results in 3.5GB of total usable memory. It just so happens that KSP's crash stage is at 3.5GB, which in this system I wouldn't expect KSP to use EVERY single MB of that memory. Windows itself reserves at least 500MB of memory for operational purposes on any Windows install, although extensions to Windows and other programs can increase the amount of memory the system requires as a reserve to run correctly and smoothly

The problem here is that, on 32bit Windows, KSP can only use 2 GB of RAM, not 4 or 3.5 or any of the other numbers bandied about.  The only real solution to running on Win32 is to reduce the texture resolution in KSP's settings to minimum (or possibly setting the command line option to force dx11 or opengl mode, not sure if these still use a lot less memory).
